<Content>A 'curate's egg' hotel. First the good points.Great location with easy access from outside Barcelona - especially by car - although the urban motorways get jammed in the rush hours. Also easy to get to most of the tourist places downtown. Good public transport - buses and Metro stop nearby.Free off-road overnight parking across the road. Meters go off at 20:00 and come on at 09:00.Great breakfast buffet spread - including delicious hot scrambled eggs! Friendly bar attached - open late. Useful vending machines with (cold) snacks and drinks.Very friendly staff - many English speakers.Now the negatives.VERY thin walls to bedrooms - not much better than cardboard. Room decoration VERY tired and in need of updating. The bathtub (in the room I had!) was really only a 'deep' shower tray. OK for me, but no use for anyone wanting to lounge in the water for an hour or so!Because of the location, it seems to be on the main route for the emergency services! They do seem to quieten them somewhat at night, but they are still audible.So, in summary, I'd say above average for services, but definitely below average for room quality. 
