<Author>Overtheline
<Content>Wish I liked it better, but alas, it was just adequate.... The price was dirt cheap (about $60 per night including breakfast for two) per night for our 5 night stay. Don't expect much and you won't be disappointed. While our room was badly needing a re-do, it was clean. The location is it's best selling point. You really can walk to most everything of interest. Metro stop is next door, Estacio de Franca is around the corner and the Marinas are just up the street (but not the cruise port - it's a short cab ride away).A few of the staff are down right surly, but the few that shine make it tolerable. It is a very noisy place.Don't expect english on the TV - just CNN and maybe a sports channel.Bottom line - it's fine for one or two nights, but if you're staying longer, find something a little nicer that you can look forward to returning to at the end of a long day of touring the city.The following has nothing to do with the hotel:A final warning about Barcelona - BEWARE OF PICKPOCKETS! One night while on la Rambla a group of young asian girls approached and surrounded us offering us sex, all the while passing their hands over you looking for your wallet. Managed to escape that attempt only to get stung the next day. While in a small square where cafe tables were set up for a couple of restaurants, a guy approached and said something was all over the back of my jacket and pants. From what I could see it looked like vomit (or worse) and when he offered to wash it off (in the restroom of the restaurant) I let him lead me there. While brushing whaterver it was, he was expertly checking all the usual spots where tourists think they can cleverly hide their wallets from crooks. My wallet was in a zipped pockets in the lining of my jacket. Within 2 minutes of his departure I realized my wallet was lone gone and so was the crook. It took me about 15 minutes to walk to the police station and the very first thing they had me do was to call the credit card companies. In just that short period of time, the crook had managed to charge over $1,000 to one of my cards!!!A little advice.....Keep a record of your credit card numbers in a seperate place.DON'T carry your social security card! - EVER!Keep a photo copy of all your documents in a seperate bag on let your travel partner carry them. 
