<Author>SDWanderlust
<Content>Holes Everywhere Location:Not located in the old city. About 10 min walk to the Las Rambla, the launching pad for most travelers. Metro station is about 3 minute walk from hotel. Also, there are a bit of things to see and do around the hotel-the Barceloneta and the Port areas. Overall, the location is great. The room:It was a mixed bag. I got an old room. It was really bad. There were holes everywhere; on the wall, the floor, the ceiling. Since I had a single room, it was understandably smaller than usual double. Because of the poor lay out of the room, it was really dark. Say, during the daytime, if you were to read something, you would have to have the light turned on. The walls were very dirty looking. The bathroom was very small. There was mildew everywhere on the shower stall. The door was also very thin therefore I heard everything when someone talking in the hallway. Unfortunately, there other young travelers, it got very loud. The room was very appalling. Granted that it was a two star establishment, it really was beyond my belief when I first saw it. However, the common areas, such as the breakfast room and the reception area, were very nice. Those were recently renovated. I suspect that renovated rooms would be in much better shape. Service:The folks at front desk were always nice and friendly for the most part. The same can be said about folks at the breakfast buffet. Regarding the breakfast buffet, choices were very limited. I had toast and jam everyday. There were hard-boiled eggs. There was also salad, something I thought was rather odd. Salad for breakfast? There were cold cuts. However, there was no fruit of any kind. The OJ was very diluted. I think it was just water and some yellow color they put in. Recommendation:I would not recommend this place unless you know for sure that you will get recently renovated room. I paid about 55 euros per night for a single, which I think was neither excessive nor cheap. 
