<Author>travellaklb
<Content>renovated or not..... My husband and I booked a trip to barcelona which included flight and accomodation. Originally we were going to just book our flight and wing the accomodation. Its a good thing we did not because Aug is prime season and there are no vacancies anywhere in Barcelona (if you dont like millions of tourists then avoid Barcelona in Aug). When trying to decide on where to stay we looked at reviews on tripadvisor. Hotel Oasis got mixed reviews and we decided to take a chance. When we arrived we realised why there were mixed reviews, half the hotel is renovated and the other half is a glorified hostel. The hotel fails to mentiont that in their website and when booking. Unfortunately we got the glorified hostel which was clean, specially the bathroom but overall the room was very rundown. Our bed we beyond uncomfortable and we complained to the hotel. The hotel was fully booked and there was no way to move rooms. After 3 days we moved to the renovated area at no extra cost. The front desk was very understanding and helpful. The breakfast was very basic but had variety (breads, cheeses, hardboiled eggs, cereals,fruit etc) and kept us full. The location was really awesome, 10min walk to La Rambla and the beach. Barcelona is a very big city and we highly recommend renting bikes and doing a bike tour. The Spanish cuisine is nothing to brag about but if you stay off main streets (specially La Rambla), you can find a decent meal. We also recommend going to cities outside Barcelona like Girona and Figueres. 
