<Content>Old versus refurbished I'm surprised by some of the recent reviews here but I guess it depends on which part of the hotel you're in. My friend  I stayed here recently and booked via different websites; I was on a refurbished floor but she wasn't. My room was a twin whilst hers was a small single even though we both paid similar amounts (although breakfast wasn't included in mine). So I suppose it's best to check what you're getting when you book because they were quite different. My room seemed clean and well presented, especially for a two star hotel. The shower and TV both worked well (always a good sign!). Other facilities were okay: there was aircon  a hairdryer but no mini-bar/fridge to store cold drinks in, no kettle, no room safe, no room service. The receptionist we dealt with was very helpful. And the staff at breakfast seemed very on top of things - the buffet (8 EUR) was well supplied with cereals, coffee, tea, hot chocolate, pastries, rolls, etc. A good start to the day!The hotel location was excellent, just 5-10 mins walk from the train station, near La Ramblas and also near the beach  marina. 
