<Content>Nice hotel, despite the problems! Despite the excellent reviews this hotel has had, I had to give it a lower rating because we had some problems. There were some downsides as well as upsides to our stay in this hotel. The downsides were:- When we arrived to the hotel the entire reception area was being renovated and looked like a building site - not a good first impression- Our room looked out onto what can be best described as a tiny, enclosed inner courtyard so we had very little daylight and fresh air- We had no hot water for the first day, which we were told was due to some work being carried out on the gas pipes in the street- On the second day of our stay we were woken up by incredibly noisy building work at 8:30 in the morning! On the upside:- The rooms were clean, nicely furnished and comfortable- The staff were friendly and helpful and when we eventually complained we were given a new room, which looked out onto the street and was thus light, airy, quiet and had hot water!- The breakfasts were abundant and tasty- The location is ideal! Not only is the hotel 10 mins walk away from La Rambla but its also less than 5 mins walk away from the train station (Estacio dela Franca) which has excelent links to the airportIn summary, I think we were a little unlucky, and if you were to go at a different time, when there are no building works or problems with hot water, you would have a very pleasant stay. 
