<Author>TWOWILLS
<Content>Enjoyable City Break We spent a four day city break, Mon 2nd till Thurs 5th May and stayed at the Oasis Hotel. After reading two of the previous reviews for April I was very worried about this booking as my 70 year old (though fairly fit) sister was accompanying my husband and myself.However we were pleasantly surprised when we got to our rooms. Our double room (third floor) was quite small but very clean and comfortable with air con (which did work if you tried) TV, phone, nice bathroom with hair dryer and large make up mirror, soap, shampoo. Plenty of clean white towels.Our bed was clean and comfortable. My sister was on the floor below and her twin room was larger and she had absolutely no complaints considering what we had paid for the trip.We had been informed that there was an ongoing refurbishment programme and the lift would not be in use. However the service lift would be in operation, hence my sister being on a lower floor.Our rooms were the Superior or Comfort rooms and had obviously been newly refurbished. Not sure if the intention is to refurbish and upgrade all the hotel rooms. I think it would be a good idea as the only complaint we had was that there was no safety deposit box ( we left our money and passports in the Reception safe) and we would have liked a brighter bedside lamp for reading at night.Breakfast was the usual continental type breakfast which we thought was adequate and there was also a tapas/bar and restuarant. We ate out but did have a couple of drinks each night in the bar.This hotel is only about a ten minute stroll from La Ramblas and lots of other attractions and right next door to the metro. The railway station is also round the corner though we didn't realise this till later and took a taxi from the airport. About 23 euros, so split three ways was far easier way to get direct to your hotel.Walls probably are quite thin but I think this is the same in most 2/3 star hotels, certainly the ones we have stayed in in Paris and Amsterdam. The only noise we heard was the cleaner in the morning which we didn't have a problem with as it was about time to get up anyway and also the noise of running water from toilet and showers above and below. First morning I did think it was water running down the wall but after that didn't really notice it.All in all we had a wonderful break with lovely warm weather. For a 2 star hotel we were very happy with the standard and location of the hotel. All the staff were fine and tried to be helpful. We would have no hestitation in staying at the Oasis again if/when we go back to Barcelona. 
