<Author>Citroenfamily1
<Content>The Perfect Surprise! We booked a triple room for ourselves and our small grandson way back in July through Easyjet, paying just over 拢200 for four nights for the three of us. Bearing in mind this bargain price, we expected to only be given one of the standard, unimproved rooms and after reading some of the recent reviews, I even tried to upgrade to a superior room without success.  Imagine, then, our surprise and delight, when, on arriving on February 7th, we were given an electronic key to Room 419 which turned out to be a spacious, recently refurbished superior triple room. The room was very well furnished with three large, comfortable beds, a desk and chair and still enough space to sit and move around easily. A small balcony was accessible through double glazed patio doors with a view across the street and to the square behind. The bathroom was simply beautiful; better than our own at home! The only thing that was missing was tea and coffee making facilities but we had taken our own kettle and cups so this was no problem. I cannot comment on the other rooms in the hotel, of course, but it is fair to say that as works of improvement are obviously still ongoing it will probably be a while before these are complete and the other rooms brought up to the same standard.  Other reviewers have mentioned noise as a problem, but the traffic noise, whilst all that you would expect from a four lane main thoroughfare and busy crossroads just outside the hotel, was cut down considerably by the double glazing and never stopped us from sleeping. (Ambulances are very obvious, and frequent, however; there must be a large hospital nearby). We simply didn't hear a sound from other residents; we only knew that we had any neighbours when we saw them in the corridor.  The staff were very friendly and helpful and the room was spotlessly cleaned and the beds made every day with fresh towels in the bathroom. The breakfast was fine, eaten in a pleasant breakfast room and more than enough to set you up for the day. There is also a decent little bar and restaurant, which we used on our first night, but, to be fair, with a six year old, the food was a little wasted on him and we had to rely on the joys of the local burger and sandwich bars (of which there are plenty nearby).  The situation of the hotel is perfect with some of Barcelona's most interesting sights very close by. The Bus Turistic stops 100 yards away (the two day tickets are excellent value) and this gives you access to most of Barcelona. Many of the best sights are well within walking distance and the city seems reasonably safe (although be careful of handbags and cameras as my wife nearly had hers taken on Montjuc by two guys on a motorbike - just don't leave anything lying unattended for any length of time. Sadly, its the same in any city nowadays, I suppose.)  All - in - all, we had a wonderful time and were very sad to leave our room, and Barcelona, behind. I cannot fault the Hotel Oasis in any way and would recommend it to anyone, especially having regard to the amazing value that it offers. Hopefully, we will return to Barcelona one day and we certainly will not be looking further than the Hotel Oasis and Room 419!  
