<Content>Very good value for money We stayed 4 nights from 26th to 30th of January in a superior room (double). We booked from Hotelscentral - for slightly more than 30 euro per person per night this is definitely a great choice if your budget is not too high and you prefer saving some money for a good restaurant instead of wasting money in a hotel. The rooms and furnitures are quite new. The breakfast (buffet) is better than other three or four stars hotel I have visited. Only drawbacks: as the room was almost on Placa de Palau you could hear some noises in the morning due to traffic. Further the curtains of the room allow some light to enter when the sun rises (only for people who needs absolute darkness to sleep). Apart these minor drawbacks I would definitely recommend this hotel and the superior rooms. The other good point of Hotel Oasis is its position: Barceloneta metro station is 100m far, bus stop is just outside the hotel. And above all the hotel is located between the Barri Gotic and Port Vell so the location is perfect. There is also a restaurant where you can eat for 8 to 12 euro depending on the day (more expansive in the week-end). We never tried it but if you are too tired to find a restaurant (however there are many quite close to the hotel in the Barri Gotic) this is another plus of Hotel Oasis. If I will return in Barcelona I will definetely stay there. 
